[BID 4N] ⟦You ask for keycards with Roman Key Card Blackwood for hearts — the four aces and the \HK.⟧ Your partner answers 5\C, showing one or four of the five keycards.
[BID 5D] ⟦You continue the slam try with 5\D and ask for the trump queen and any kings.⟧ Your partner shows the \HQ and the \SK, confirming the trump suit is solid and the spade honor is working.
[BID 6H] ⟦You bid 6\H, confident the missing ace cannot sink the slam.⟧
[show NS]South held \SJ74 \HAKJT7 \DAQ83 \CK — strong trumps, the diamond ace-queen, and the club king. The pair was off the \SA, but the king-ask reply located the \SK opposite South's small spades. With the spade tops covering South's holding, the suit yields just one loser, and 6\H brings in twelve tricks.}
